dcterms:creator: C. J. C. H. Watkins
P. Dayan
dcterms:description: Q-learning is a fundamental reinforcement learning algorithm that has been extensively studied for its convergence properties.
dcterms:title: Q-learning

dcterms:creator: J. N. Tsitsiklis
dcterms:description: Asynchronous Q-learning is a variant of Q-learning that allows for updates to be made asynchronously, improving efficiency in certain scenarios.
dcterms:title: Asynchronous Q-learning

dcterms:creator: H. V. Hasselt
dcterms:description: Double Q-learning is an enhancement of Q-learning that mitigates the overestimation bias by maintaining two separate value estimates.
dcterms:title: Double Q-learning

dcterms:creator: M. G. Azar
R. Munos
M. Ghavamzadeh
H. J. Kappen
dcterms:description: Speedy Q-learning introduces a momentum term to accelerate the learning rate compared to traditional Q-learning.
dcterms:title: Speedy Q-learning

dcterms:creator: D. Lee
N. He
dcterms:description: Periodic Q-learning mimics stochastic gradient-based training schemes with periodic target updates to improve learning stability.
dcterms:title: Periodic Q-learning

dcterms:creator: D. Lee
J. Hu
N. He
dcterms:description: Finite-time analysis of Q-learning provides insights into the convergence behavior of Q-learning under a discrete-time switching system framework.
dcterms:title: Finite-time analysis of Q-learning
